Nice to meet you, I am Emanuele, 31 years old, from Milan (Italy).

I have been living in Geneva for more than 5 years, working between the private and non profit sector.

I recently settled down in a lovely flat in the old town, one of the most beautiful and central areas of Geneva. Quality, functionality, good taste and sobriety, are some of the principles that inspire me, and i tried to furnish my apartment accordingly... a combination of antique and modern furniture, many plants and all the technology needed to make my flat convenient (high speed wi-fi, washing+drying machine, smart TV, internet radio, nice lights, etc.).

I often go to Milan over the weekend which is when I mainly rent my flat.
Differently from other hosts that rent their properties for speculative reasons, I am just trying to have a little contribution to my monthly expenses and to allow other people enjoying Geneva while staying in a beautiful and convenient place. 
You will notice that the quality of the furnitures is probably higher, the kitchen equipment is richer and, as an example, there are boardgames and all my books in a nice shelf in my room (with you can play with or read if you fancy).
So, I will be happy to share my apartment with you... as long as you commit to treat it with the care you would use with your own!
